  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd : \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2 \u0bb0\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bc7 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bae\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bb0\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc7 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3 \u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Train services will continue as normal: Only a few train services will be delayed - General Manager, Railway Department",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The fuel shortage has brought the public transport services to a complete standstill. Commuters faced major inconvenience as railway unions went on strike for two hours during the day demanding priority in fuel supply.",
        "Railways General Manager Tammika Jayasundara said that despite the fact that most commuters rely entirely on rail services, train services have to be continued amidst challenges.",
        "A few railway unions have warned that they will engage in a series of strike action if the fuel issue is not resolved.",
        "Following the escalation of fuel shortage in the country, the train service has been declared as an essential service and the gazette has been issued as the fuel supply has been advised to be for essential services only till the next 10th.",
        "The unions pointed out that we have repeatedly urged the authorities to provide fuel facilities for the trains to run the trains, but the authorities have not paid any attention to it.",
        "Several train services were canceled today as railway unions engaged in a two-hour walkout today, which has affected the unionization of services. There were also delays in train services.",
        "Train services from Kottai and Maradana railway stations were suspended today due to the strike.",
        "Also, an official of the Fort Railway Station mentioned that the train which was going to depart from the Fort Railway Station towards Kangesanthurai was delayed by one and a half hours.",
        "Due to the shortage of fuel, the service of the train service has been affected. KU Konthasinghe, President of the Railway Engine Operating Association, said that it was completely wrong for any of our unions to go on strike at a time when the whole country was facing a crisis situation.",
        "Fort railway station was in a state of disarray today due to the cancellation and delay of train services."
      ],
